Baseline confirmed: test fails at line 19 because the workflow is unimplemented. I have read every file in the repo. Here is the complete report.

---

## 1. Full Directory Tree

```
workspace/
├── AGENTS.md
├── README.md
├── package.json
├── tests-before.log              (frozen baseline failure log)
├── data/
│   └── collections.json          (the seed/fixture — in-memory JSON, NOT a live DB)
├── migrations/
│   └── 001_collection_contract.mongodb.js
├── schema/
│   ├── access-paths.md
│   └── schema.md
├── src/
│   ├── portal-view.mjs           (read-only projection — DO NOT need to change)
│   ├── render-proof.mjs          (artifact/SVG renderer — not under test)
│   └── workflow.mjs              ← THE ONLY FILE TO IMPLEMENT
└── tests/
    └── acceptance.test.mjs       (the contract — must NOT be changed)
```

No `node_modules`, no lockfile. **Zero dependencies.** Pure Node ESM (`"type": "module"`), Node v24.15.0.

## 2. package.json (verbatim)

```json
{
  "name": "ast-bench-strategic-account-rescue-mongo",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "private": true,
  "type": "module",
  "scripts": {
    "test": "node tests/acceptance.test.mjs",
    "render": "node src/render-proof.mjs"
  }
}
```

Test command: `npm test` → `node tests/acceptance.test.mjs`. No test framework — uses `node:assert`.

## 3. Database / MongoDB connection

**There is NO real MongoDB, no `mongodb-memory-server`, no mock, no driver.** Despite the "mongo" lane naming and the MongoDB MCP server being available, the actual code operates on a **plain JS object loaded from `data/collections.json`** via `JSON.parse(readFileSync(...))`. The `db` argument passed to `applyBenchmarkTask(db, now)` is just that parsed object with array properties (`db.workflow_requests`, `db.workflow_state`, etc.). "Persistence" means **pushing into the in-memory arrays on that object**. The `migrations/001_collection_contract.mongodb.js` is a cosmetic artifact (just `db.createCollection(...)` calls) and is never executed by the tests. **You do not need MongoDB at all to implement or pass this.**

## 4. The test contract — `tests/acceptance.test.mjs` (verbatim, this is what must pass)

```js
